   <text type="letter">
      <body>

         <opener>
            <dateline><name type="place" rend="right">Washington, D.C.,</name><date
                  when="1867-08-10" rend="right">10 August 1867.</date></dateline>
            <salute rend="left">W. L. Alden.</salute>
            <salute rend="left">My dear Sir:</salute>   
         </opener>
         <p>Your note has been received.<ptr target="prc.00091_n2"/>&#8212;Accept&#8212;for
            yourself, the <hi rend="italic">Citizen</hi>, &amp; Gen. Halpine<ptr
               target="prc.00091_n3"/>&#8212;My sincere thanks for your kindness. I fully appreciate
            it.</p> <p>As I have not at my control, at this moment, any bound copies of <hi
               rend="italic">Leaves of Grass</hi>, would you allow me to send you a copy in paper
            I forward it by same mail with this.<ptr target="prc.00091_n4"/></p>
         <p>I send best remembrances to the General.</p>
         <closer rend="right">
            <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
         </closer>

      </body>
   </text>
